@Chapter
    @Title { Reference: Wizards }
    @Tag { reference.wizards }
@Begin
@BeginSections
@Section
    @Title { Introduction }
    @Tag { introductionxxxxx }
@Begin
@LP
In @QDR, some of the toolbars, menu options and templates
invoke wizards to take you step-by-step through particular tasks.
In this chapter we explain each @QDR wizard.

@End @Section
@Section
    @Title { Main Window Wizard }
    @Tag { main.window.wizard }
@Begin
@LP
The Main Window Wizard is invoked by
clicking the Main Window form template in the 
@NamePageRef{new.file.dialog}. This wizard helps you to create a main
window with actions, menu options and toolbars.


@BeginSubSections
@SubSection
    @Title { Choose Available Menus and Toolbars }
    @Tag{choose.available.menus.and.toolbars}
@Begin
@Figure
    @Caption { The Main Window wizard }
    0.45 @Scale @IncludeGraphic { "images/qd-mainwinwzd.eps.gz" }
@LP
The 'Choose available menus and toolbars' wizard page appears
first. It presents three categories of default actions, File
Actions, Edit Actions and Help Actions. For each category you
can choose to have @QDR create menu items, toolbar
buttons and signal"/"slots connections for the relevant actions.
You can always add or delete actions, menu items, toolbar buttons
and connections later. Check or uncheck the checkboxes to reflect
your preferences.

@LP
Click @Option{Next} to move on to the next wizard page.

@End @SubSection
@SubSection
    @Title { Setup Toolbar }
    @Tag{setup.toolbar}
@Begin
@Figure
    @Caption { The Main Window wizard's Setup Toolbar tab }
    0.45 @Scale @IncludeGraphic { "images/qd-mainwinwzdpage2.eps.gz" }
@LP
The Setup Toolbar  wizard page is used to populate a toolbar
with actions from each of the default action categories. Click
the Category combobox to select which set of actions you wish
to work on. The Actions listbox lists the actions available for
the current category. The Toolbar listbox
lists the toolbar buttons you want to create. Click the blue left and
right arrow buttons to move actions into or out of the Toolbar list
box. Click the blue up and down arrow buttons to move actions up and
down within the Toolbar list box. Note that the '<Separator>' item in
the Actions list box may be moved to the Toolbar list box as often as
required and will cause a separator to appear in the finished toolbar.

@LP
Click @Option{Back} if you want to return to the 'Choose available
menus and toolbars' wizard page. Click @Option{Finish} to populate
the main window and to exit the wizard. Click @Cancel on any
of the wizard pages to leave the wizard without making any changes.

@End @SubSection
@EndSubSections
@End @Section
@Section
    @Title { Data Table Wizard }
    @Tag { data.table.wizard }
@Begin
@LP
The Data Table Wizard is automatically invoked by clicking the
datatable widget and placing it on the form. The datatable widget
is used to create tabular views of database data.

@BeginSubSections
@SubSection
    @Title { Choose the Database and Table }
    @Tag{choose.the.database.and.table}
@Begin
@LP
The Choose the Database and Table wizard page appears first.
The available databases are displayed in the 'Database Connection'
listbox. Choose a connection by clicking it. If there are no
connections listed in the listbox, click @Option{Setup Database Connections}
to invoke the @NamePageRef{edit.database.connections.dialog}. The 'Table' listbox
shows all the tables and views that are available through the
selected database connection. Select a table or view by clicking
it.

@Figure
    @Caption { The Data Table wizard }
    0.45 @Scale @IncludeGraphic { "images/qd-datatablewzd.eps.gz" }
@LP
Click @Option{Next} to move on to the next wizard page.

@End @SubSection
@SubSection
    @Title { Displayed Fields }
    @Tag{displayed.fields}
@Begin
@Figure
    @Caption { The Data Table wizard's Displayed Fields tab }
    0.45 @Scale @IncludeGraphic { "images/qd-datatablewzdpage2.eps.gz" }
@LP
The Displayed Fields  wizard page is
used to select fields that will be displayed in the table. By default,
every field except the table or view's primary key, is initially
placed in the 'Displayed Fields' list. Click the blue left and right
arrow buttons to move fields from the 'Available Fields' listbox and
into or out of the Displayed Fields
listbox. Click the blue up and down arrow buttons to move fields up
and down within the 'Displayed Fields' listbox. The order in which
fields appear in the 'Displayed Fields' listbox is the order they are
shown in the Data Table, with the top-most field being in the
left-most column.

@LP
Click @Option{Next} to move on to the next wizard page. Click @Option{Back}
if you want to return to the @NamePageRef{choose.the.database.and.table}
wizard page.

@End @SubSection
@SubSection
    @Title { Table Properties }
    @Tag{table.properties}
@Begin
@Figure
    @Caption { The Data Table wizard's Table Properties tab }
    0.45 @Scale @IncludeGraphic { "images/qd-datatablewzdpage3.eps.gz" }
@LP
The Table Properties wizard page is used to set the Data Table's
initial editing options. Check the 'Read-Only' checkbox to prevent
records from being edited, deleted or added. Check the checkboxes
in the 'Confirmations' section to force the user to confirm their
changes. By default users must confirm deletions. Click 'Allow
column sorting' to allow the user to sort the data by clicking
a column's header (which displays the field name).

@LP
Click @Option{Next} to move on to the next wizard page. Click @Option{Back}
if you want to return to the Displayed Fields wizard page.

@End @SubSection
@SubSection
    @Title { SQL }
    @Tag{sql}
@Begin
@LP
The 'SQL' wizard page is used to apply filters and sorts to the
data in the table. Click the 'Filter' line edit and enter a valid
SQL @Code{WHERE} clause without the WHERE keyword. The
filter applies to the data shown in the table.

@LP
To sort the available fields in the table, click the blue left
and right arrow buttons to move fields from the 'Available Fields'
listbox into or out of the 'Sort By' listbox. Click the blue
up and down arrow buttons to move fields up and down within the
'Sort By' listbox. Click the @Option{A-Z} button to change the sort
order of the selected field in the 'Sort By' listbox from ascending
to descending and vice versa.

@LP
Click @Option{Next} to move on to the next wizard page. Click @Option{Back}
if you want to return to the @NamePageRef{table.properties} wizard page.

@Figure
    @Caption { The Data Table wizard's SQL tab }
    0.45 @Scale @IncludeGraphic { "images/qd-datatablewzdpage4.eps.gz" }
@End @SubSection
@SubSection
    @Title { Finish }
    @Tag{finish}
@Begin
@Figure
    @Caption { The Data Table wizard's Finish tab }
    0.45 @Scale @IncludeGraphic { "images/qd-datatablewzdpage5.eps.gz" }
@LP
The 'Finish' wizard page is used to select auto-editing and to
leave the wizard. If you want user edits, e.g. inserts and updates,
to be automatically applied when the user navigates to another
record, check the 'AutoEditing' checkbox. If 'AutoEditing' is
unchecked, users must press @Option{Enter} to confirm their edit before
moving to another record, or their edit will be lost.

@LP
Click @Option{Finish} to create the datatable widget with all of the
options you selected in the wizard. Click @Option{Back} if you want
to return to the 'SQL' wizard page. Click @Cancel on any of
the wizard pages to leave the wizard without making any changes.

@End @SubSection
@EndSubSections
@End @Section
@Section
