@LP
The Choose the Database and Table wizard page appears first.
The available databases are displayed in the 'Database Connection'
listbox. Choose a connection by clicking it. If there are no
connections listed in the listbox, click @Option{Setup Database Connections}
to invoke the @NamePageRef{edit.database.connections.dialog}. The 'Table' listbox
shows all the tables and views that are available through the
selected database connection. Select a table or view by clicking
it.

@LP
Click @Option{Next} to move on to the next wizard page.

@End @SubSection
@SubSection
    @Title { Displayed Fields }
    @Tag{displayed.fieldsx}
@Begin
@LP
The Displayed Fields wizard page is used to select fields that
will be displayed in the table. Click the blue left and right
arrow buttons to move fields from the 'Available Fields' listbox
